# But where does helper() come from?

This is the part beginners struggle with.

We write another function.

```java
TreeNode helper(int[] nums, int left, int right)
```

This function says

> "Give me any part of the array.

I'll build a BST from that part."

---

# Example

Suppose

```java
helper(nums,0,6)
```

means

```text
[1 2 3 4 5 6 7]
```

It returns

```text
        4
```

---

Now

```java
helper(nums,0,2)
```

means

```text
1 2 3
```

It returns

```text
    2
   / \
  1   3
```

---

Now

```java
helper(nums,4,6)
```

means

```text
5 6 7
```

Returns

```text
    6
   / \
  5   7
```

Notice something?

The same function works for **every subarray**.

That's why recursion is perfect here.

